  "text": "Intake brings free stream air into the engine. Also, the intake sits upstream of the compressor and, while the inlet does not work on the flow, inlet performance has a strong influence on engine net thrust, [NASA Glenn Research Centre]. Intake feeds air at the compressor face at a Mach number in the range 0.3 to 0.5 with minimum turbulence [CITATION_1] .",
